The paper deals with the detection of a stochastic process in noise, which is a problem in signal processing and information theory. The use of stochastic differential equations (SDE) and the Kalman filter suggest a focus on control and systems theory (cs.SY) and signal processing (cs.SP). The paper also discusses the use of sensor networks, which falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The use of statistical methods and hypothesis testing suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and statistics (cs.ST).
